# Markdown link syntax

When **creating or editing** Markdown in this repository, use **standard Markdown links** only: `[link text](url)`.

- **Do not** use raw HTML for navigation links, e.g. `<a href="...">...</a>`.
- **Do not** rely on angle-bracket autolinks like `<path/to/note.md>` for cross-note links; use `[title](path/to/note.md)` instead.

This keeps body links consistent and aligned with vault tooling that recognizes Markdown link destinations.
